影响我们对城市、工作，

350
00:14:57.895 --> 00:14:59.832
and the way we live.
和我们的生活方式的设计。

351
00:14:59.832 --> 00:15:02.378
We will get where we're going faster
我们将能更快地到达目的地，

352
00:15:02.378 --> 00:15:05.376
and society will recapture vast amounts
社会也将会夺回大量

353
00:15:05.376 --> 00:15:06.667
of lost productivity
为了治理交通污染

354
00:15:06.667 --> 00:15:10.308
now spent sitting in traffic basically polluting.
而失去了的生产力。

355
00:15:10.308 --> 00:15:13.581
But why now? Why do we think this is ready?
但为什么是现在？我们为什么认为已经准备好了？

356
00:15:13.581 --> 00:15:15.775
Because over the last 30 years,
因为在过去的30年间，

357
00:15:15.775 --> 00:15:17.823
people from outside the automotive industry
从事汽车行业以外的人

358
00:15:17.823 --> 00:15:19.931
have spent countless billions
花费了数亿的资金

359
00:15:19.931 --> 00:15:21.666
creating the needed miracles,
创造所需要的奇迹，

360
00:15:21.666 --> 00:15:24.538
but for entirely different purposes.
但目的确完全不同。

361
00:15:24.538 --> 00:15:27.166
It took folks like DARPA, universities,
这是通过像DARPA、大学， （DARPA：美国国防部高级研究计划局）

362
00:15:27.166 --> 00:15:30.330
and companies completely outside of the automotive industry
和与汽车产业完全无关的 企业的那些人

363
00:15:30.330 --> 00:15:32.631
to notice that if you were clever about it,
来注意到，如果你机灵点，

364
00:15:32.631 --> 00:15:35.161
autonomy could be done now.
自动驾驶现在可以实现了。

365
00:15:35.161 --> 00:15:38.544
So what are the five miracles needed for autonomous vehicles?
那么自驾车辆所需的五个奇迹是什么？

366
00:15:38.544 --> 00:15:40.187
One, you need to know
第一，你需要知道

367
00:15:40.187 --> 00:15:42.921
where you are and exactly what time it is.
你所处的位置与现在的时间。

368
00:15:42.921 --> 00:15:45.329
This was solved neatly by the GPS system,
这由GPS系统完美地解决了，

369
00:15:45.329 --> 00:15:46.641
Global Positioning System,
全球定位系统，

370
00:15:46.641 --> 00:15:49.307
that the U.S. Government put in place.
由美国政府落实了。

371
00:15:49.307 --> 00:15:51.830
You need to know where all the roads are,
你需要知道所有的路都在哪里、

372
00:15:51.830 --> 00:15:54.733
what the rules are, and where you're going.
有什么规则，和你要去哪。

373
00:15:54.733 --> 00:15:57.316
The various needs of personal navigation systems,
对于私人导航系统的各种需求，

374
00:15:57.316 --> 00:15:59.071
in-car navigation systems,
车载导航系统，

375
00:15:59.071 --> 00:16:02.104
and web-based maps address this.
和网络的地图解决了这个问题。

376
00:16:02.104 --> 00:16:04.731
You must have near-continuous communication
你必须拥有

377
00:16:03.341 --> 00:16:06.624
with high-performance computing networks
与高性能计算网络和与附近其他人的

378
00:16:06.624 --> 00:16:08.294
and with others nearby
几乎无间断的交流

379
00:16:08.294 --> 00:16:11.609
to understand their intent.
才能了解他们的意图。

380
00:16:11.609 --> 00:16:14.717
The wireless technologies developed for mobile devices,
为移动设备所开发的无线技术，

381
00:16:14.717 --> 00:16:16.510
with some minor modifications,
加上一些小的修改，

382
00:16:16.510 --> 00:16:19.469
are completely suitable to solve this.
完全可以解决这个问题。

383
00:16:19.469 --> 00:16:21.959
You'll probably want some restricted roadways
若要开始，你可能需要一些

384
00:16:21.959 --> 00:16:23.149
to get started
受限的道路，

385
00:16:23.149 --> 00:16:25.627
that both society and its lawyers
从而让社会和律师们

386
00:16:25.627 --> 00:16:27.499
agree are safe to use for this.
都同意它的使用是安全的。

387
00:16:27.499 --> 00:16:29.348
This will start with the HOV lanes
这将从高乘载车道开始

388
00:16:29.348 --> 00:16:31.481
and move from there.
然后扩张。

389
00:16:31.481 --> 00:16:34.032
But finally, you need to recognize
但你最终需要辨认

390
00:16:34.032 --> 00:16:36.135
people, signs and objects.
人、 路标和物体。

391
00:16:36.135 --> 00:16:39.189
Machine vision, special sensors, and high-performance computing
机器视觉、特殊传感器，与高性能计算

392
00:16:39.189 --> 00:16:40.761
can do a lot of this,
都可以做到一大部分，

393
00:16:40.761 --> 00:16:43.319
but it turns out a lot is not good enough
但事实证明一大部分是不够的，

394
00:16:43.319 --> 00:16:45.260
when your family is on board.
因为你的家人的安全也由它掌握着。

395
00:16:45.260 --> 00:16:48.781
Occasionally, humans will  need to do sense-making.
人们将时不时地需要开动脑筋。

396
00:16:48.781 --> 00:16:52.393
For this, you might actually have to wake up
为此，你可能真的要去把你的乘客叫醒

397
00:16:52.393 --> 00:16:54.489
your passenger and ask them what the hell
并且询问他们

398
00:16:54.489 --> 00:16:57.291
that big lump is in the middle of the road.
马路中间的那一大块是什么鬼东西。

399
00:16:57.307 --> 00:16:59.651
Not so bad, and it will give us a sense of purpose
这不算太糟糕， 而且会在这个新的世界

400
00:16:59.651 --> 00:17:01.504
in this new world.
赋予我们一种使命感

401
00:17:01.504 --> 00:17:04.244
Besides, once the first drivers explain
再说了，一旦第一个司机解释

402
00:17:04.244 --> 00:17:05.570
to their confused car
给他们困惑的车说

403
00:17:05.570 --> 00:17:08.236
that the giant chicken at the fork in the road
那个挡在分岔口的巨型小鸡

404
00:17:08.236 --> 00:17:09.779
is actually a restaurant,
其实是一家餐厅，

405
00:17:09.779 --> 00:17:12.083
and it's okay to keep driving,
并告诉它没关系，继续开车，

406
00:17:12.083 --> 00:17:15.503
every other car on the surface of the Earth
从那时开始，地球表面上一半的车辆

407
00:17:15.503 --> 00:17:18.425
will know that from that point on.
都会了解这一点。

408
00:17:18.425 --> 00:17:20.688
Five miracles, mostly delivered,
五个奇迹，差不多都到齐了，

409
00:17:20.688 --> 00:17:22.566
and now you just need a clear vision
而现在你唯独需要一个清晰的视野，

410
00:17:22.566 --> 00:17:25.403
of a better world filled with autonomous vehicles
能看到一个遍地是自驾车辆的世界，

411
00:17:25.403 --> 00:17:29.016
with seductively beautiful  and new functional designs
它们的设计散发着极具诱惑性的美丽 并拥有全新的性能，

412
00:17:29.016 --> 00:17:31.470
plus a lot of money and hard work
再加上大量的钱和辛苦的劳动，

413
00:17:31.470 --> 00:17:33.066
to bring it home.
才能把它变成现实。

414
00:17:33.066 --> 00:17:36.088
The beginning is now only a handful of years away,
它的开始相对现在只有几年的距离了，

415
00:17:36.088 --> 00:17:37.956
and I predict that autonomous vehicles
而且我预测自驾车辆

416
00:17:37.956 --> 00:17:40.027
will permanently change our world
将永久地改变我们的世界，

417
00:17:40.027 --> 00:17:44.211
over the next several decades.
就在接下来的几十年间。

418
00:17:44.211 --> 00:17:46.863
In conclusion, I've come to believe
作为总结，我开始相信

419
00:17:46.863 --> 00:17:49.101
that the ingredients for the next Pantheons
建造下一个万神殿的材料

420
00:17:49.101 --> 00:17:50.488
are all around us,
就在我们身边，

421
00:17:50.488 --> 00:17:52.675
just waiting for visionary people
只是在等待有远见的人，

422
00:17:52.675 --> 00:17:54.409
with the broad knowledge,
加上他们广泛的知识、

423
00:17:54.409 --> 00:17:56.019
multidisciplinary skills,
多学科的技能，

424
00:17:56.019 --> 00:17:57.887
and intense passion
和想要运用它们

425
00:17:57.887 --> 00:18:02.973
to harness them to make their dreams a reality.
从而把梦想变成现实的强烈热情。

426
00:18:02.973 --> 00:18:05.469
But these people don't spontaneously
但这些人不是自然地

427
00:18:05.469 --> 00:18:06.808
pop into existence.
就蹦出来了。

428
00:18:06.808 --> 00:18:08.647
They need to be nurtured and encouraged
他们需要从小开始

429
00:18:08.647 --> 00:18:10.426
from when they're little kids.
就加以培育和鼓励。

430
00:18:10.426 --> 00:18:12.286
We need to love them and help them
我们要爱护他们并且帮助他们

431
00:18:12.286 --> 00:18:14.005
discover their passions.
发现他们的热情所在。

432
00:18:14.005 --> 00:18:16.219
We need to encourage them to work hard
我们需要去鼓励他们努力工作

433
00:18:16.219 --> 00:18:18.656
and help them understand that failure
并帮助他们理解失败

434
00:18:18.656 --> 00:18:21.527
is a necessary ingredient for success,
是成功的必要因素，

435
00:18:21.527 --> 00:18:23.708
as is perseverance.
毅力也是如此。

436
00:18:23.708 --> 00:18:26.806
We need to help them to find their own role models,
我们需要帮助他们找到自己的榜样，

437
00:18:26.806 --> 00:18:29.478
and give them the confidence to believe in themselves
并给他们能够相信自己

438
00:18:29.478 --> 00:18:32.255
and to believe that anything is possible,
和一切皆有可能的信心，

439
00:18:32.255 --> 00:18:35.764
and just as my grandpa did when he took me shopping for surplus,
正如我爷爷的带着我去淘 盈余商品的时候，

440
00:18:35.764 --> 00:18:37.547
and just as my parents did
正如我的父母带我

441
00:18:37.547 --> 00:18:39.569
when they took me to science museums,
去科学博物馆的时候，

442
00:18:39.569 --> 00:18:42.850
we need to encourage them to find their own path,
我们需要鼓励他们去找自己的路，

443
00:18:42.850 --> 00:18:45.507
even if it's very different from our own.
即使它与我们自己的不同。

444
00:18:45.507 --> 00:18:46.915
But a cautionary note:
但要警惕的是：

445
00:18:46.915 --> 00:18:49.349
We also need to periodically pry them away
我们还需要定期地把他们

446
00:18:49.349 --> 00:18:50.818
from their modern miracles,
与现代的奇迹分开，

447
00:18:50.818 --> 00:18:52.789
the computers, phones, tablets,
比如计算机、 手机、 平板电脑、

448
00:18:52.789 --> 00:18:54.383
game machines and TVs,
游戏机和电视机，

449
00:18:54.383 --> 00:18:56.627
take them out into the sunlight
带他们去沐浴阳光

450
00:18:56.627 --> 00:18:58.756
so they can experience both the natural
从而让他们有机会体验自然

451
00:18:58.756 --> 00:19:01.653
and design wonders of our world,
与我们世界、我们星球，

452
00:19:01.653 --> 00:19:03.895
our planet and our civilization.
和我们文明的设计奇观。

453
00:19:03.895 --> 00:19:06.822
If we don't, they won't understand
如果我们不这样，他们就无法理解

454
00:19:06.822 --> 00:19:08.704
what these precious things are
这些珍贵的东西是什么，

455
00:19:08.704 --> 00:19:11.299
that someday they will be resopnsible
这些将是他们在未来某天有义务

456
00:19:11.299 --> 00:19:13.581
for protecting and improving.
去保护和改善的东西。

457
00:19:13.581 --> 00:19:15.224
We also need them to understand
我们还需要他们理解

458
00:19:15.224 --> 00:19:18.253
something that doesn't seem adequately appreciated
一件在我们越发依赖科技的世界里

459
00:19:18.253 --> 00:19:20.716
in our increasingly tech-dependent world,
似乎没有被充分领会的事，

460
00:19:20.716 --> 00:19:22.399
that art and design
就是艺术与设计

461
00:19:22.399 --> 00:19:24.312
are not luxuries,
不是奢侈品，

462
00:19:24.312 --> 00:19:26.138
nor somehow incompatible
也不是跟科学与工程

463
00:19:26.138 --> 00:19:28.007
with science and engineering.
无法兼容的。

464
00:19:28.007 --> 00:19:33.582
They are in fact essential to what makes us special.
事实上，只有它们才能让我们如此特别。

465
00:19:33.582 --> 00:19:36.097
Someday, if you get the chance,
某一天，如果你有机会，

466
00:19:36.097 --> 00:19:37.634
perhaps you can take your kids
或许你可以把你的孩子

467
00:19:37.634 --> 00:19:39.405
to the actual Pantheon,
带到真正的万神殿，

468
00:19:39.405 --> 00:19:42.065
as we will our daughter Kira,
就像我们会把我们的女儿Kira

469
00:19:42.065 --> 00:19:44.143
to experience firsthand
带去亲身体验

470
00:19:44.143 --> 00:19:48.400
the power of that astonishing design,
那令人震惊的设计所带来的力量，

471
00:19:48.400 --> 00:19:52.144
which on one otherwise unremarkable day in Rome,
这让在罗马本是平凡普通的一天，

472
00:19:52.144 --> 00:19:55.171
reached 2,000 years into the future
延伸到了未来两千年后，

473
00:19:55.171 --> 00:19:57.829
to set the course for my life.
并为我的人生设定了方向。

474
00:19:57.829 --> 00:19:59.960
Thank you.
谢谢。

475
00:19:59.960 --> 00:20:04.268
(Applause)
